5 Subject: Domestic relations; penalty for desertion or nonsupport
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to repeal the
7 criminal penalty for failure of an adult child to support the adult child’s parent
8 if that parent is destitute and unable to support themselves.
9 An act relating to filial support
10 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
11 Sec. 1. 15 V.S.A. § 202 is amended to read:
12 § 202. PENALTY FOR DESERTION OR NONSUPPORT
13 A married person who, without just cause, shall desert or willfully neglect
14 or refuse to provide for the support and maintenance of his or her the person’s
15 spouse and children, leaving them in destitute or necessitous circumstances or
16 a parent who, without lawful excuse, shall desert or willfully neglect or refuse
17 to provide for the support and maintenance of his or her the child or an adult
18 child possessed of sufficient pecuniary or physical ability to support his or her
19 parents, who unreasonably neglects or refuses to provide such support when
20 the parent is destitute, unable to support himself or herself, and resident in this
